          <h4 class="mt-3">What is a Spaced Repetition System?</h4>
          <p>
            Spaced Repetition is a tried and tested technique that helps you learn, <i>fast</i>. ðŸŒ 
          </p>
          <p>
            Unlike how you may have used flashcards in the past, the principle of Spaced Repetition is <i>not</i> for you to review as many cards as possible, as often as possible, in the hope that the information will stick.
          </p>
          <p>
            With Spaced Repetition, you are shown your flashcards as <i>infrequently</i> as possible. Numerous studies have shown that the ideal time for your brain to be challenged to recall informations is when that piece of information is just at the tip of your tongue, and you have to struggle to remember it. 
          </p>
          <p>
            That's when you have the maximum opportunity to strengthen the pathways in your brain leading to this piece of information. ðŸ§ 
          </p>
          <p>
            In short, spaced Repetition helps you <i>learn</i> information for good, in a time-efficient way.
